All Classes

Class Summary
Class Description
BuyStuffWindow
The window for purchasing goods/upgrades from an island's shop
CommandInput
Class that contains all the command line input stuff.
descriptionMaker
A class that processes the raw information and turns that into descriptions/text that the player can read.
GameEnvironment
The game environment that actually, well, contains the game.
GameEnvTest
Tests on the GameEnvironment class
GameOver
The window that appears at the end of the game
GameStats
A class that holds most of the game's data and info.
Good
The Good subclass of item - for goods that the player can sell and buy.
GoodTest
Tests on the Good class
Island
The Island class, representing the islands the player can sail to.
IslandTest
Tests on the Island class
IslandWindow
The window to represent an island that the player is on
Item
The item superclass, which covers both Upgrades and Goods
ItemTest
Tests on the Item class
MainMenu
The Main Menu of the game Is essentially a title screen and a start button.
PreGame
The GUI window that gets the setup prompts from the player, those being Their Trader name Their Choice of Ship Their desired duration of days
QuitWindow
A simple quit window that asks if a user wants to quit the program.
RandomEvent
The random events of the game.
RandomEventTest
Tests on the RandomEvent class
Route
The Route class, representing the route the player takes to travel to different Islands.
RouteTest
Some simple testing on the Route class Mainly testing if the route generated has the intended variables stored
runGame
The command line version of the game
runGameTest
Activating the Commandline version of the game
SailingEvent
The window that displays and runs random events during a player's voyage
SelectSail
The window for choosing an island to sail to, as well as a route, and then setting sail.
SellStuffWindow
The window for selling goods to an island's shop
Ship
The ship class, representing the ship that the player sails around in.
ShipTest
Tests on the Ship class
ShipView
The window for viewing the properties, cargo and sales of a ship
UiManager
The program that manages all the different windows and ensures they co-operate
Upgrade
The ship upgrades that the player can purchase for their ship throughout the game.
UpgradeTest
Tests on the Upgrade class
ViewIslands
The window for looking at all islands currently in the game As well as their shops and routes
